Kanti GALA, an individual; et al., Plaintiffs-counter-defendants-Appellants, v. William B. BRITT, an individual; et al., Defendants-counter-claimants-Appellees. No. 11-15111. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Argued and Submitted March 16, 2012. Filed April 4, 2012. Paul R. Connaghan, Esquire, Connaghan Newberry Law Firm, Las Vegas, *644NV, Richard Charles Hopkins, Jr., Esquire, Hopkins Legal Counsel, LLC, Boulder, CO, for Plaintiffs-counter-defendants-Appellants. James William Blue, Jr., Northern Blue LLP, Chapel Hill, NC, Paul Georgeson, McDonald Carano Wilson, LLP, Reno, NV, for Defendants-counter-claimants-Appellees.

Before: WALLACE and BEA, Circuit Judges, and BENNETT, District Judge.*

The Honorable Mark W. Bennett, District Judge for the U.S. District Court for Northern Iowa, sitting by designation.

MEMORANDUM **

The district court’s judgment is VACATED. The case is REMANDED to the district court to consider whether subject matter jurisdiction exists in this matter. 28 U.S.C. § 1332; Johnson v. Columbia Prop. Anchorage, LP, 437 F.3d 894, 899 (9th Cir.2006).

This disposition is not appropriate for publication and is not precedent except as provided by 9 th Cir. R. 36-3.
